Scope of the Workshop - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Mobile agents offer unique opportunities for structuring and implementing distributed systems . A wide range of applications has been indicated for mobile agent technology , including electronic commerce , telecommunications services , network management , group work and work flow management .
The Second Workshop on Mobile Agents follows the successful MA'97 held in Berlin . The purpose of this workshop is to provide a forum for the presentation and discussion of research work in the area of mobile software agents . Contributions are solicited in the fields of mobile agent models and languages , agent systems , as well as applications of mobile agent technology .
Areas of interest include , but are not limited to : - Mobile agent models and architectures - Languages for mobile agents - Mobile agent systems - Agent control and management - Agent communication and cooperation - Agent mobility management and persistence - Security aspects - Electronic payment and agents - Fault tolerance - Transactional agents - Applications of mobile agents , such as electronic commerce , telecommunications services , management , active networks , etc
Information For Authors - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Authors are invited to submit original ( not submitted or published elsewhere ) full papers to the address given below . The submission should not exceed 5000 words . The front page should contain the names of the authors , the corresponding author 's affiliation , address , phone , fax and email address , as well as an abstract . By submission through email , send the uuencoded , compressed , postscript files to
ma 98 - submissions @ informatik . uni-stuttgart . de
or send four copies of your manuscript by mail to
Kurt Rothermel , MA'98 submissions , Universitaet Stuttgart , IPVR , Breitwiesenstr . 20 / 22 D- 70565 Stuttgart , Germany
One of the authors of each accepted paper is supposed to present the paper at the workshop .
